{"id":1268147413,"question_id":3444,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"2 weeks, 3 days","timestamp":1716695963,"status":11,"status_display":"Wrong Answer","runtime":"N/A","url":"/submissions/detail/1268147413/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Find the Number of Good Pairs II","memory":"N/A","code":"class Solution {\n    public long numberOfPairs(int[] nums1, int[] nums2, int k) {\n        \n        Arrays.sort(nums1);\n        Arrays.sort(nums2);\n        \n        int m = nums1.length;\n        int n = nums2.length;\n        long cnt = 0;\n        \n        Map<Integer, Integer> map1 = new HashMap<>();\n        Map<Integer, Integer> map2 = new HashMap<>();\n        \n        for(int i=0; i<m; i++){\n            if(nums1[i]%k!=0) continue;\n            \n            map1.put(nums1[i], map1.getOrDefault(nums1[i],0)+1);\n            \n        }\n        \n        for(int j=0; j<n; j++){\n            map2.put(nums2[j]*k, map2.getOrDefault(nums2[j]*k,0)+1);            \n        }\n        \n        List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>(map1.keySet());\n        \n        for(int i=list.size()-1; i>=0; i--){\n            int k1 = list.get(i);\n            for(int k2 : map2.keySet()){\n                \n                if(k2>k1) break;\n                \n                if(k1%k2==0   ){\n                    cnt+= (map1.get(k1)*map2.get(k2));\n                    \n                }\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return cnt;\n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"find-the-number-of-good-pairs-ii","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
